send mail by installing ssmpt then configuring /etc/ssmtp/ssmtp.conf and
/etc/ssmtp/revaliases. Then run mail.

receive mail by configuring getmail (see ~./.getmail/getmailrc. All that is needed at first is getmailrc and a directory to save mail to along with the three subdirectories within it). and then running getmail -q.

-q = quiet

save attachments using metamail or mpack